1ï¸âƒ£ Linux Basics (Must-Know)
Q1. What is Linux?
Expected:
Linux is an open-source Unix-like OS kernel used in servers, cloud platforms, containers, and embedded systems.

Q2. Difference between Linux and Unix?
Linux	               Unix
Open-source	         Mostly proprietary
Free	               Paid
Large community	     Vendor-controlled

Q3. What is the Linux Kernel?
Expected:
Core of OS responsible for:
Process management
Memory management
Device drivers
System calls

Q4. What is a shell?
Expected:
A command-line interpreter that interacts with the kernel.
Examples: bash, sh, zsh

Q5. Common Linux directory structure
Directory	Purpose
/	Root
/bin	Essential binaries
/etc	Config files
/var	Logs & variable data
/home	User home dirs
/tmp	Temporary files
/opt	Optional software

